page.title: 13ECOLOGY
page.content: About half of the area is covered by Forestry Commission plantations. Most of these are coniferous woodland. There is also some heathland and in the lower part of this there is an area of bog which has many sundews growing there. In the woods there are deer, foxes and many other animals as well as the usual insects. There are also many wild flowers and of the woodland is covered by a dense undergrowth of ferns and brambles. The Forestry Commission is responsible for most of the conservation in this area.
